===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[feeling]] of [[contempt]] or [[scorn]].
#: {{ux|en|The cat viewed the cheap supermarket catfood with '''disdain''' and stalked away.}}
#* '''2018''' June 24, Sam Wallace, "[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/24/england-vs-panama-world-cup-2018-live-score-latest-updates/ Harry Kane scores hat-trick as England hit Panama for six to secure World Cup knock-out qualification]," ''Telegraph'' (UK) <small>(retrieved 24 June 2018)</small>:
#*: Everything that could go right for England did although they never felt lucky and they chuckled at {{w|Harry Kane|Kane}}’s third that ricocheted off his heel while he was looking the other way. Somewhere in the Moscow outskirts one could only guess at the grand '''disdain''' {{w|Cristiano Ronaldo}} will have felt at being supplanted as the tournament’s top scorer in that manner.
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Ado|3|1|passage='''Disdain''' and scorn ride sparkling in her eyes.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} That which is [[worthy]] to be disdained or regarded with contempt and [[aversion]].
#* {{RQ:Spenser Faerie Queene|canto=I|book=I|passage=Most loathsom, filthy, foul, and full of vile '''Disdain'''.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} The state of being despised; shame.
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 6-3|3|3|passage=The leaves and fruit maintain'd with beauty's sun ; Exempt from envy , but not from '''disdain'''}}

